Preheat your oven to 220°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} to the boil. Cut the @potatoes{450%g} (no need to peel) into 1/2cm slices. Add it to the pan, lower the heat and simmer until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> TIP: The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through the middle. Be careful - you don't want the potato slices to break up too much!

Drain in a #colander{} and set aside to steam dry.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into small pieces). Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and chopped into small pieces) (no need to peel!), quarter lengthways, then chop widthways into small pieces. Halve, then remove the core and seeds from the @yellow pepper{1}(halved, cored and seeds removed) and chop into small pieces. Roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{75%g}(roughly chopped). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1 can} in a #sieve{}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2 bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the onion and carrot and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the pepper and mushrooms, along with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring, until soft, ~{5%minutes}.

Next, add the lentils, @Provençal herbs{1%tsp} and @tomato purée{15%g} to the pan and stir well. Pour in the @water{100%ml} along with the @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp}. Add the @wholegrain mustard{1/2%tsp}, then stir in the @baby spinach{125%g} a handful at a time until wilted. Simmer for ~{1%minute} then add half of the parsley.

> Add less mustard if you don't like heat!

Transfer the lentil mixture from the pan into an #ovenproof dish{}. Once the potatoes are cool enough to handle, arrange on top of the pie, overlapping each slice of potato. Season with a few grinds of @black pepper{a few grinds}. Grate the @half-fat mature cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated) on top then bake on the top shelf of your oven until bubbling and golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Let the hotpot sit for a few mins and then serve in #deep bowls{}. Finish with a sprinkling of the remaining parsley. Enjoy!